## Warning: Paket 'EnrichedHeatmap' wurde unter R Version 4.2.3 erstellt
## See system.file("LICENSE", package="MotifDb") for use restrictions.
ah <- AnnotationHub(localHub=FALSE)
## snapshotDate(): 2022-10-31
ensdb <- ah[["AH89211"]] # mouse ensembldb object
## loading from cache

Downloading Data and prepare tracks (code provided during class)

options(timeout=6000)
download.file("https://ethz-ins.org/content/w7/atac.chr19.bam", "atac.chr19.bam")
download.file("https://ethz-ins.org/content/w7/atac.chr19.bam.bai", "atac.chr19.bam.bai")
# if you're on a slow computer, you might also want to download the tracks that we're generating below:
download.file("https://ethz-ins.org/content/w7/w7_bw.zip", "w7_bw.zip")
unzip("w7_bw.zip")
bam <- "atac.chr19.bam"

# create a track using all fragments, computing the coverage at each position (and force Ensembl naming)
bam2bw(bam, output_bw = "full_cov.bw", paired=TRUE, binWidth=10L, forceSeqlevelsStyle = "Ensembl")
# create a track using all fragments, but computing the number of cuts/insertion sites at each position
bam2bw(bam, output_bw = "full_cuts.bw", paired=TRUE, binWidth=1L, type="ends", forceSeqlevelsStyle = "Ensembl")
# create a track using only nucleosome-free fragments, computing coverage
bam2bw(bam, output_bw = "NF_cov.bw", paired=TRUE, binWidth=1L, minFragLength=30, 
       maxFragLength=120, forceSeqlevelsStyle = "Ensembl")
# create a track using only nucleosome-free fragments, computing cuts
bam2bw(bam, output_bw = "NF_cuts.bw", paired=TRUE, binWidth=1L, minFragLength=30,
       maxFragLength=120, type="ends", forceSeqlevelsStyle = "Ensembl")
# create a track using only mono-nucleosome fragments, computing coverage
bam2bw(bam, output_bw = "mono_cov.bw", paired=TRUE, binWidth=1L, minFragLength=140,
       maxFragLength=220, forceSeqlevelsStyle = "Ensembl")
# create a track using only mono-nucleosome fragments, computing cuts
bam2bw(bam, output_bw = "mono_cuts.bw", paired=TRUE, binWidth=1L, minFragLength=140,
       maxFragLength=220, type="ends", forceSeqlevelsStyle = "Ensembl")

Looking for Motif of interest

# we prepare the list of tracks
tracks <- c("Full cuts"="full_cuts.bw", "NF coverage"="NF_cov.bw", "NF cuts"="NF_cuts.bw",
            "Mono cov"="mono_cov.bw", "Mono cuts"="mono_cuts.bw")
genome <- ah[["AH68356"]]
## loading from cache
## require("rtracklayer")
# get the sequence for chr19:
chr19 <- GRanges("19", IRanges(1L,seqlengths(genome)["19"]))
chr19 <- setNames(getSeq(genome, chr19), "19")

For GCR

# We just get the first motif
gcr_motif <- query(MotifDb, c("GCR","Mus"))[[1]]
# lets have a look at it
view_motifs(gcr_motif)

motifs_gcr <- findMotifInstances(chr19, gcr_motif)
## Note: motif [motif] has an empty nsites slot, using 100.
## 
moi_gcr_conf <- motifs_gcr[motifs_gcr$score>15]

Plotting the unnormalised tracks (GCR)

# extracting of  signals around the motif occurences
# zooming in to 500bp around the motif centers, in windows of 5bp
sm_gcr <- signal2Matrix(tracks, moi_gcr_conf, w=5, extend=500)
## Reading full_cuts.bw
## Reading NF_cov.bw
## Reading NF_cuts.bw
## Reading mono_cov.bw
## Reading mono_cuts.bw
plotEnrichedHeatmaps(sm_gcr, trim=0.95)

### After normalising (GCR)

sm_gcr <- renormalizeBorders(sm_gcr)
plotEnrichedHeatmaps(sm_gcr, trim=0.95)

## For Rest

# We just get the first motif
rest_motif <- query(MotifDb, c("REST","Mus"))[[1]]
# lets have a look at it
view_motifs(rest_motif)

motifs_rest <- findMotifInstances(chr19, rest_motif)
## Note: motif [motif] has an empty nsites slot, using 100.
moi_rest_conf <- motifs_rest[motifs_rest$score>15]

Plot the unnormalised tracks (Rest)

# extract signals around the motif occurences
# we zoom in to 500bp around the motif centers, in windows of 5bp
sm_rest <- signal2Matrix(tracks, moi_rest_conf, w=5, extend=500)
## Reading full_cuts.bw
## Reading NF_cov.bw
## Reading NF_cuts.bw
## Reading mono_cov.bw
## Reading mono_cuts.bw
plotEnrichedHeatmaps(sm_rest, trim=0.95)

### Plots after normalising (Rest)

sm_rest <- renormalizeBorders(sm_rest)
plotEnrichedHeatmaps(sm_rest, trim=0.95)
